Task 1: Add Image Quality Checker
First, scroll to the very top of the file. Find the line that says:

text
import warnings
Copy and paste this RIGHT AFTER it:

text
def check_image_quality(image_array):
    brightness = np.mean(image_array)
    if brightness < 50:
        return False, "Image too dark"
    if brightness > 220:
        return False, "Image too bright"
    return True, "Good quality"
